329
00:20:15.257 --> 00:20:17.384
Not bad for Whitman.

330
00:20:17.551 --> 00:20:20.053
Hey, look,
we got a visitor.

331
00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:22.931
I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to interrupt.

332
00:20:23.098 --> 00:20:25.893
Well, don't apologize,
come on up here, darling.

333
00:20:26.059 --> 00:20:29.271
We could use a little something here
besides the smell of lumber.

334
00:20:30.814 --> 00:20:32.316
Dad,
this is Allison Hamilton.

335
00:20:32.482 --> 00:20:33.901
Allison,
I'm glad to meet you.

336
00:20:34.067 --> 00:20:35.110
- Allie.
- Allie.

337
00:20:35.277 --> 00:20:36.570
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. Calhoun.

338
00:20:36.737 --> 00:20:38.864
Well Mr. Calho...
What, am I old or something?

339
00:20:39.031 --> 00:20:40.490
You can call me Frank.

340
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:42.701
- Here, come in and have a seat.
- Okay.

341
00:20:43.869 --> 00:20:46.330
So, Allie.
Well, yeah, she is pretty, son.

342
00:20:46.497 --> 00:20:49.082
- Yes.
- She's a lot prettier than you let on.

343
00:20:49.249 --> 00:20:51.084
- Oh, is that right?
- No, it's not right.

344
00:20:51.251 --> 00:20:52.336
Don't believe what he says.

345
00:20:52.503 --> 00:20:54.963
- What is this you got?
- Umm, I... uh, I just...

346
00:20:55.130 --> 00:20:56.298
I brought you something.

347
00:20:56.465 --> 00:20:59.426
Let me see.
Let's have a look.

348
00:20:59.593 --> 00:21:01.470
- Did you do this?
- Mm-hmm.

349
00:21:01.637 --> 00:21:03.305
Well, that's beautiful.
Look at that.

350
00:21:03.472 --> 00:21:05.140
That's a damn picture there.

351
00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:09.269
Well, I know just where we can
put that, thank you.

352
00:21:09.436 --> 00:21:11.897
Oh, that was
a lovely poem.

353
00:21:12.064 --> 00:21:13.482
What was it?

354
00:21:13.649 --> 00:21:15.108
- EI...
- Whitman.

355
00:21:15.275 --> 00:21:18.695
See when he was a little kid
he used to stutter real bad.

356
00:21:18.862 --> 00:21:21.281
- Dad...
- So... well, you did.

357
00:21:21.448 --> 00:21:23.408
- I didn't know that.
- God. I stammered.

358
00:21:23.575 --> 00:21:24.868
Stammered, stutter,
what's the difference?

359
00:21:25.035 --> 00:21:27.663
Couldn't understand
a damn thing he said.

360
00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:30.999
So, I got him to read me poetry
out loud.

361
00:21:31.166 --> 00:21:32.501
It wasn't
very pretty at first,

362
00:21:32.668 --> 00:21:33.794
but then his stutter
went away.

363
00:21:33.961 --> 00:21:35.754
Well, it's a good idea,
that poetry.

364
00:21:35.921 --> 00:21:37.297
- Yeah, I thought so.
- Huh?

365
00:21:37.464 --> 00:21:40.133
Unbelievable,
unbelievable.

366
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:42.636
I'm a Tennyson man,
myself, but he likes Whitman...

367
00:21:42.803 --> 00:21:44.513
For some reason,
I don't know.

368
00:21:44.680 --> 00:21:47.099
Say, how would you like some breakfast?
Would you like some breakfast?

369
00:21:47.266 --> 00:21:48.642
- Breakfast?
- Yeah.

370
00:21:48.809 --> 00:21:51.061
- Dad, it's 10:00.
- What's that got to do with it?

371
00:21:51.228 --> 00:21:53.397
You can have pancakes
any damn time of night you want.

372
00:21:53.564 --> 00:21:56.483
- Come on, you want some breakfast?
- Sure.

373
00:21:57.818 --> 00:22:00.821
It was an improbable romance.

374
00:22:00.988 --> 00:22:04.700
He was a country boy.
She was from the city.

375
00:22:04.867 --> 00:22:06.493
She had the world
at her feet,

376
00:22:06.660 --> 00:22:08.829
while he didn't have
two dimes to rub together.

377
00:22:13.667 --> 00:22:15.210
Noah, come on.

378
00:22:16.336 --> 00:22:17.379
Whoo!

379
00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:19.631
Look at us.

380
00:22:22.259 --> 00:22:23.385
What are we doing?

381
00:22:23.552 --> 00:22:26.430
Do you think in another life,
I could have been a bird?

382
00:22:28.515 --> 00:22:29.516
What do you mean?

383
00:22:29.683 --> 00:22:31.810
Like reincarnation.

384
00:22:32.853 --> 00:22:34.563
I don't know.

385
00:22:34.730 --> 00:22:36.315
I think I could.

386
00:22:42.696 --> 00:22:43.947
Say I'm a bird.

387
00:22:45.073 --> 00:22:46.492
No.

388
00:22:46.658 --> 00:22:48.535
- Don't do it.
- Say I'm a bird.

389
00:22:48.702 --> 00:22:50.537
Stop it. Stop it now.

390
00:22:50.704 --> 00:22:52.498
- You're not.
- Say it!

391
00:22:54.458 --> 00:22:57.002
- You're a bird.
- Yeah.

392
00:23:02.716 --> 00:23:04.551
Now say
you're a bird too.

393
00:23:07.304 --> 00:23:09.473
If you're a bird,
I'm a bird.

394
00:23:43.006 --> 00:23:45.050
- Come on, darling.
- What are you doing?

395
00:23:45.217 --> 00:23:46.885
Don't.
Don't!

396
00:23:56.937 --> 00:23:58.438
Here we go,
on the count of three, okay?

397
00:23:58.605 --> 00:24:00.983
Real easy,
on three, ready?

398
00:24:01.149 --> 00:24:02.609
- Okay, okay.
- One...

399
00:24:02.776 --> 00:24:04.903
- Two... two...
- two...

400
00:24:05.070 --> 00:24:06.488
...three!
- No! I can't.

401
00:24:06.655 --> 00:24:08.740
Get in the water!

402
00:24:08.907 --> 00:24:10.951
- Get in! I'm sorry.
- Come on, chicken.

403
00:24:11.118 --> 00:24:12.911
Get in the water, baby.
Baby, would you get in.

404
00:24:13.078 --> 00:24:14.955
- Get in the water.
- I can't.

405
00:24:15.122 --> 00:24:16.456
- Go!
- Get in the water!

406
00:24:16.623 --> 00:24:17.791
- One...
- Come on, jump.

407
00:24:17.958 --> 00:24:20.002
- Two...
- Three.

408
00:24:30.971 --> 00:24:33.098
Keep 'em together!
No, no, no.

409
00:24:33.265 --> 00:24:35.017
- Get to your place.
- Down here.

410
00:24:35.184 --> 00:24:37.519
And move.
And keep it.

411
00:24:37.686 --> 00:24:38.562
No, don't move it!

412
00:24:38.729 --> 00:24:40.480
I don't understand
what you're talking about.

413
00:24:40.647 --> 00:24:42.983
They didn't agree on much.

414
00:24:43.150 --> 00:24:45.819
In fact, they rarely agreed on
everything. They fought all the time.

415
00:24:45.986 --> 00:24:47.446
- Don't kick me!
- Don't push me.

416
00:24:47.613 --> 00:24:49.865
And they challenged
each other every day.

417
00:24:50.032 --> 00:24:51.992
But despite
their differences,

418
00:24:52.159 --> 00:24:54.953
they had one
important thing in common.

419
00:24:55.120 --> 00:24:57.748
They were crazy
about each other.

420
00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:01.001
